the diagnosis really easy.

396
00:29:46,534 --> 00:29:48,512
Prison infirmary isn't known
for stellar record keeping.

397
00:29:48,536 --> 00:29:50,372
And we can't exactly
ask the patient.

398
00:29:50,497 --> 00:29:52,207
Yeah, that
would've been pre-coma.

399
00:29:52,415 --> 00:29:54,960
But how could you have known
that it would affect her that way?

400
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:57,295
We didn't think we had
anything mysterious until...

401
00:29:57,379 --> 00:29:59,464
What about renal cancer
throwing clots?

402
00:29:59,547 --> 00:30:01,383
Urinalysis was
negative. That's too bad.

403
00:30:01,883 --> 00:30:04,386
'Cause that was my
one big idea. Really?

404
00:30:08,723 --> 00:30:09,849
House?

405
00:30:13,103 --> 00:30:14,229
House, you there?

406
00:30:16,398 --> 00:30:18,900
Tell me more about the patient.

407
00:30:18,984 --> 00:30:20,568
What was she doing
before prison?

408
00:30:20,694 --> 00:30:23,154
She was a cop, shot
a kid in self defense,

409
00:30:23,238 --> 00:30:25,740
never got over the guilt, started
taking drugs and got busted.

410
00:30:26,074 --> 00:30:27,450
Way to bury the lead.

411
00:30:27,701 --> 00:30:29,077
How long ago was this shooting?

412
00:30:29,202 --> 00:30:30,245
I'm not sure. Why?

413
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:33,498
Again, you assumed she's
had Hep-C for 10 years.

414
00:30:33,581 --> 00:30:35,059
But if you find out
when she shot the kid,

415
00:30:35,083 --> 00:30:36,727
you'll find out when
she started taking drugs,

416
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:38,837
and when she actually
contracted the Hep-C.

417
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,213
And you think this is relevant?

418
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:42,590
